From: Eric Auger <eric.auger@redhat.com>
Date: Thu, 19 Jan 2017 20:57:50 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 33/64] iommu: Only map direct mapped regions

Git-commit: 544a25d904cab2ae68bd71b334603ec3a49b60dd
Patch-mainline: Queued
Git-repo: git://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/next/linux-next.git
References: fate#321947

As we introduced new reserved region types which do not require
mapping, let's make sure we only map direct mapped regions.

Signed-off-by: Eric Auger <eric.auger@redhat.com>
Reviewed-by: Tomasz Nowicki <tomasz.nowicki@caviumnetworks.com>
Tested-by: Tomasz Nowicki <tomasz.nowicki@caviumnetworks.com>
Tested-by: Bharat Bhushan <bharat.bhushan@nxp.com>
Signed-off-by: Will Deacon <will.deacon@arm.com>
Signed-off-by: Mian Yousaf Kaukab <yousaf.kaukab@suse.com>
---
 drivers/iommu/iommu.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/iommu/iommu.c b/drivers/iommu/iommu.c
index 980f04e7cde8..933db03c7d23 100644
--- a/drivers/iommu/iommu.c
+++ b/drivers/iommu/iommu.c
@@ -355,6 +355,9 @@ static int iommu_group_create_direct_mappings(struct iommu_group *group,
 		start = ALIGN(entry->start, pg_size);
 		end   = ALIGN(entry->start + entry->length, pg_size);
 
+		if (entry->type != IOMMU_RESV_DIRECT)
+			continue;
+
 		for (addr = start; addr < end; addr += pg_size) {
 			phys_addr_t phys_addr;
 
